'''Ethics''' is a major branch of [[philosophy]], encompassing proper conduct and good living. It is significantly broader than the common conception of ethics as the analyzing of right and wrong. A central aspect of ethics is "the good life", the life worth living or that is simply satisfying, which is held by many philosophers to be more important than [[Morality|moral]] conduct.<ref>Singer, P.
